track_notes: A long round in the Far Eastern Fells which includes 9 other Wainwright Summits as well as High Street. GPS track dates from September 2009.
track_title: High Street from Hartsop with 9 Wainwrights

track_notes: A big round from Kentmere Church (parking limited) which includes 8 Wainwright summits plus High Street. GPS track is from April 2010.

This walk starts from the Kirkstone Pass Inn and traverses Stoney Cove Pike, Thornwaite Crag (LDW-043), High Street and finally Knott (LDW-066). The walk was done with tow cars in Nov 2012. A summer bus service (508) runs up the Kirkstone Pass. This could assist if you just have one car.
track_title: Linear walk Stoney Cove Pike and High Street

track_notes: Nice circular walk.  Car parking can be difficult at the end of Haweswater - arrive early!  Riggigdale Crag is slight scramble.
track_title: High Street - From Haweswater - Small Water - Ill Bell - Riggingdale Crag

track_notes: Total time (including ops): 5hr 45m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards.
